        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>San Francisco</placeName>
                <date>Jany 17<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1862</date>.</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">No doubt ere<lb/> this reaches you the news of my misfortune<lb/>
                has been made known to you tho' the public<lb/> press truly may I say with
                    <add>שלוחהא דרחמנא</add><lb/>
                <add>ירושלים</add>!<lb/> probably in a short time you will be visited by<lb/>
                <persName>Rabbi Nissan</persName> the <add>Hebrew</add> from <add>Hebrew</add><lb/>
                who will bring you a letter and a parcel from<lb/> me, your <date>December</date>
                number has reached me<lb/> I have ventured to send you a communication<lb/>
                containing <hi rend="underline">facts</hi> and signed it “<hi rend="underline"
                        ><persName>Theophilus</persName></hi>”<lb/> I assure you that all the good
                we try to do is<lb/> counteraded<add>?</add> by the parties therein named, of<lb/>
                course I do not wish my name in the matter, but<lb/> you can rely on the statement
                there made. I hope<lb/> you will notice it and reply to the Questions put<lb/> in
                the able manner you generally do in all such<lb/> cases, as it will do much good for
                the cause of our<lb/> holy Religion. In truth I must tell you that <persName>Dr<lb/>
                    Cohn</persName> will not be guilty of such acts although<lb/> he is the radical
                reformer, because I know<lb/> he has refused there things as already stated</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>I try all in my power to uphold Ancient<lb/> Judaism and it grieves me to see
                such<lb/> atrocities by these men, they defy every body<lb/> and I work if possible
                to prevent a recurrence<lb/> of those acts. You know well <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> I
                hope you will send me some more <hi rend="underline">Occident</hi><lb/> of the <hi
                    rend="underline">back nos</hi> if you can and in your<lb/> next send me your <hi
                    rend="underline">Bill</hi> up to the present<lb/> and tell me how to send you
                the <hi rend="underline">money</hi><lb/> and I will do so.</p>
            <p>You will greatly favor me by sending the<lb/> Pamphlets of <persName>Messrs
                    Nathan</persName> and <persName>DeSolla</persName><lb/> in the subject of
                    <add>Hebrew</add> when I<lb/> receive them I will write an article for<lb/> you
                on the subject if you like to have it<lb/> as from the detached pieces I have
                read<lb/> I fear the right points have not been touched.<lb/> As soon as the Books
                of the <add>Hebrew</add> for<lb/> the relief of Israelites in
                    <placeName>Palestine</placeName>, I will take<lb/> care to forward certified
                copies to you.</p>
            <p>Hoping soon to hear from you</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Believe me</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Yours truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <persName role="author">H. A. Henry</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
